# How to create GitHub account:
- GitHub sign up
- Open VM and run the machine > yum -y install git > cd .ssh/ > cat id_rsa.pub > copy ID
- Profile settings > SSH and GP keys > add SSH > name and paste key
- Create repo on github > public > Checkamrk "Add README file"
- Go to code (in green color) > SSH > Copy id
- On vm server- run--- git clone git@github.com:mahmadg/linuxdmz.git
- git config --global user.name "username"
- git config --global user.email "email id"
- create a file
- git add .
- git commit -m "upgrading to new version"
- git push ( server will push the fil to github)

- git pull (server will pull the file from github)
